The Taxonomy is a classification system which aims to identify if a company’s activities are considered as environmentally sustainable.

Siemens supports the EU agenda’s general objectives of carbon neutrality by 2050 and the direction of capital flows towards sustainable activities. Siemens also supports the EU Taxonomy by improving transparency helping scale up sustainable investment and achieving the Union’s decarbon- ization and environmental objectives.

